race.comment: TARA'S LILY (1) hit the ground running from an outside draw with a fast early split, holding on for a minor placing when second and beaten 0.8 lengths at Bendigo over 500m in 27.98. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Key chance in this line up. MOONLIGHT MILLER (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (35.34) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a good record here including four wins. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. One of the main contenders. LYNDL SAID NO (7) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when third (30.69) at The Meadows and may be close to breaking through. Has a good record here at this journey. Hard to beat again. FOXY ROXY (4) defied the market to win last start and cannot be ruled out.
